   \]

   \[
   \text{Additional cows needed} = \frac{10 \text{ liters}}{5 \text{ liters/cow}} = 2 \text{ cows}
   \]

Thus, the farmer needs 2 more cows to meet the requirement of 25 liters of milk per day.
